<paragraph id="C70597710D2475516BD0B6E56711A391" blockId="5.[151,750,1152,1214]" box="[151,371,1188,1214]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
(
<figureCitation id="5F818BF40D2475516BD8B6E56687A391" box="[159,229,1188,1214]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,257,1301,1325]" captionTargetBox="[169,1419,274,1275]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[153,1430,264,1309]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Brassolis species in dorsal (left) and ventral (right) views. (A &amp; B) Male and female B. sophorae from French Guiana. (C &amp; D) Female and male B. sophorae from Ecuador. (E &amp; F) Male and female B. haenschi from Ecuador. (G) Male B. sophorae from Trinidad. (H) Male B. sophorae from Peru. (I &amp; J) Male and female B. dinizi from Paraiba and Ceará respectively (Brazil). (K) Male B. sophorae from Santa Catarina (Brazil). (L) Male B. sophorae from Paraguay." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/188450/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
